Uses of Package
RRPSS

  • Classes in RRPSS used by RRPSS 
    Class Description
    Customer
    An Object of Customer represents a single customer with relevant customer details such as name, contact number and membership status.
    Employee
    Entity class for an Employee of the Restaurant
    MainMenu
    This Class handles the implementation of the MainMenu and the resulting changes that the user can do to the said Menu.
    MenuItems
    This class is the basic/template class on which MenuItems such as MainCourse/Dessert/Drink/Package are created
    Order
    The entity class of Order made by staff on the system
    Package
    This class is a subclass of the MenuItems which wholly deals with the constituents of the Package (consisting of multiple MenuItems and the details of the Package)
    Reservation
    An object of the Reservation Class specifies the parameters of a single Reservation such as number of people who are catered to by the reservation, name of the customer creating the Reservation and the time of the specified Reservation
    TableReservations
    An Object of TableReservations represents a Table with the Unique Table Identifier, Capacity, empty state identifier and List of Reservations associated with that Table
